
Session

Process items that needs to be considered that would impact the type of activities that would be imbedded in the sessions:
    - number of participants (spectogram and activity 1. getting feedback ...)
    - duration: betwen 2 and 3 hours
    
Learning Objectives
framed with actual usage of Decidim, real life scenarios or real cases
- Knowledge
- Skills
- Attitude

Duration:
Between 100 and 120 mins 
+ Hands-on: 90 mins

Welcoming - 10 mins
- Briefly introduce yourself and the session, then ask participants to introduce themselves (quick way, name and affiliation if they feel like) and answer the following questions:  
WHAT ARE THE EXPECTATIONS OF THE SESSION
- Taking expectations into account, give a brief overview of the session, including objectives, what will be covered (and what not), and how much time is available.

After the welcoming and depending of time available, number of participants, expectations set by them and vibe in the room, facilitator can choose between three activities, however if enough time s/he can make 2 activities (beginning by spectogram)

Activity 1.Spectogram (icebreaker) - 10 mins
Make some polarizing statements to take temperature of the audience regarding beliefs regarding pol part (tecnofilia and tecnofobia, tecnofetichism, etc.) 
For instance: ?????
things to consider:
    - number of participants would impact the spectogram
    - what are the questions and how many quesitons that would make and impact to the participants
    - Create back up questions in case the participants do not come up with polarizing statements. 

AND/OR

Activity 2 PARTICIPATORY PROCESS - 20 mins
Getting feedback and sharing experiences of people on participatory processes. Listing 1 process they have been involved with. Name, objectives, who/when/where, identifying social & political processes involved and tools (analogic or digital) and micro valoration
+
things to consider:
    - is this an individual activity, by pairs or a groups
    - is this a listing or is it more visual (drawing)
    - do we do a report back?
    - do we frame the type of processes we want to talk about
ROLE FACILITATOR: HELP PEOPLE TO THINK ABOUT ON AND OFFLINE PARTICIPATION
POLITICAL PARTICIPATION IS TO GENERIC HERE. SHOULD WE LINK THIS TO POLITICAL PARTICIPATION WITH PUBLIC INSTITUTIONS.

OR

Activity 3 - BRAINSTORMING CURRENT CONNECTION TO CITY COUNCIL- 20 mins
Brainstorm with participants in order to identify and list the existing current communication/information channels with the city council (exemples: 010 telephone, city council websites, district meetings, participative processes on/off, others, decidim) 
> What is working and what is not working for them as citizens and/or for the pol processes they are engaged with
ROLE FACILITATOR: HELP PEOPLE TO THINK ABOUT ON AND OFFLINE PARTICIPATION


Discussion - 20 mins
What is online and what is offline participation. Study the limits of both on and offline. Synthesis on inherent characteristics of online and offline pol participation (prepare a reference document on this > idea is that all forms are inclusive and exclusive - there is always somebody that can not participated even if willing to > multichannel approaches). Los límites pueden no ser vistos por los grupos "principales". Por ejemplo, los hombres pueden no ver que el horario de la reunión es incompatible con la crianza, o los nacionales pueden no ver que el idioma es una barrera para inmigrantes 
FACILITATOR INTRODUCES THE DISCUSSION. START FROM EXPERIENCES, POSSIBILITIES, THE LIMITATION, HOW MANY THINGS ARE A HYBRIT. THE PRIVELEDGE OF PEOPLE WHO ARE PARTICIPATING, WHAT IS INCLUSSIVE AND EXCLUSSIVE. ADD ACTIVITY ON PRIVELEDGE 
AT THE END THE FACILITATOR SYNTESIZE THE DISCUSSION.
WHICH SPECIFIC EXERCISE WILL FIT HERE, SHOULD BE DECIDED WITH THE FACILITATOR OF TOT. WE CAN OFFER DIFFERENT STYLES HERE, AS THE ACTIVITY DEPENDS ON THE SKILLS AND CONFIDENCE OF THE FACILITATOR

Input - 15 mins
History / vision of decidim (where it comes from, basic principles, mission/aims, different process it enables > intro to representative/deliberative/direct democracy possibilities in the platform) 

Deepening - 30 mins
Departing from previous activity or activities (check if analysis of pol participation processes was achieved, if not begin deepneing by that question) > listing 1, 2, 3 political proccess they are engaged with (or close people are), then people gather in little groups and analyse the different objectives/actions/principles of their political participation process + what are the tools and processes they use to advance those objectives/actions
IS THIS IN RELATION TO THE PUBLIC INSTITUTIONS?
CHRONOLOGICAL, TOOLS AND PROCESS, THEN WE LOOK HOW DECIDIM CAN SUPPORT SOME OF THESE PARTS (DECIDIM IS ALSO SEQUENTIALLY IN TIME)
MAKE A GENERIC DOCUMENT OR TABLE OF WHAT ARE THE OPTIONS OR FUNCATIONALITIES THAT CAN BOOST IT OR HELP

DEPARTING FROM IDEAL CASE STUDIES. IN AN IDEAL WORLKD WITH CONTRAINTS. THEN THEY GO THROUGH THESE STEPS. IF YOU LAUNCH X CAN DECIDIM HELP YOU. IF IT DEPARTS FROM THEIR OWN EXPERIENCE, THERE MIGHT BE TO MUCH DETAIL AND GRANULARITY

TOMORROW TEST BOTH IDEAS OUT OURSELVES

For instance: 
OBJECTIVES/ACTIONS
    Putting an issue on public institutions agenda, 
    Amplifying an issue by involving mass media and/or public opinion, 
    Collaborative (documents, maps, investigation), 
    CONSULTATIVE PROCESS (BUDGET, DOCUMENTS, LAW, POLICIES)
    Auditing / transparency/accountability/documentation of processes, 
    Denouncing/ Leaking, 

PROCESS & TOOLS
    Organisation: internal democracy and Decision making processus (how and who take decisions)
    Communication about what you do and why you do and how people can join/engage, 
    Information/Feedback/Notification (when something is happening), 
    Collaboration/Networking: Organising among different actors/organisations/networks, 
    COLLABORATIVE WORKING /CROWDSOURCING
    Decision making processus: Consultation/Polling/Voting/Referendum/Petitions (different options about what should we do/choose)
    Follow up of actions, evaluation, impact assesment

For every process of pol participation; think about the steps/aims/objectives are included within and think about the tools and processes used to advance those steps (analogic/f2f and digital ones) (we may need a list of tools and processes for guiding the facilitator /flyers, posters, fanzines, USB keys with propaganda, comercial SNS, general assembly, meetings, referendums, etc / interesting to note that with pol part process many processes are also collective actions)

One this exercise is achieved, every group report back to the group on the most interesting elements of their conversation; ah ha moments and worries, facilitator need to distribute and moderate time wisely. S/he lists the different input and try to cluster input identifying possible questions/worries/concerns/suggestions that could be of interest for next step

Input - 10 Mins
Facilitator stresses departing from exchanges of previous activity, the different steps and/or processes of pol part where decidim could be used and be meaningful for participants and their processes + he introduces the governance of the platform, the community shaping and the metadecidim events
FOR THE INPUT WOULD IT BE AN IDEA TO SELECT ONE PROCESS OF THE PARTICIPANTS AND THEN MAP IT ONTO DECIDIM

Synthesis - 10 Mins
Facilitator invites participants to stress elements they have learned about regarding relation between online and offline participation + pol part and its interaction with tools and processes that can boost/hinder those. Importance of looking for the adequate tools/process, create multichannels and variety of tools and processes fe nabling more inclusion of diverse profiles + Reflection on the fact that political data and data is sensitive: Political vision and political intentions of the tools. Political principles. 

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
HANDS ON AND EVALAUTION DEPENDS ON IF THERE IS A DEDICATION TEAM. IF THERE IS NO DEDICATED DECIDIM FACILITATOR TEAM, THEN THE EVALUATION SHOULD BE SHORTER
QUESTION TO DECIDIM: CAN IT INCLUDE A FEEDBACK FORM. WHAT TYPE OF FEEDBACK DO THEY WANT, IN WHAT FORMAT AND WHAT SHOULD BE IN THE FEEDBACK FROM, THIS SHOULD BE DECIDED BY THE DECIDIM TEAM. THERE SHOULD BE ENOUGH SPACE FOR PARTICIPANTS TO HIGHLIGHT WHAT THEY FIND IMPORTANT 

Hands on 
IF WE DECIDE TO USE MARGRITA IDEA OF SETTING FIXED CASES FOR POLITICAL PARTICIPATION WE CAN DO THE HANDS ON, ON IMPLEMENTING THESE CASES IN DECIDIM.
 
Prepare:
1. Test out the test environment of Decidim and preprare a life demo or a show case of screenshots in case the test environment does not work
2. For the Hands-on create the cases studies studied and analised by the participants to test with or identify and explore interesting and representative existing process that are on Decidim. In the selection of the cases think of the context of the participants, highlight the different roles on the platform and present the posibilities, limitations and important points for political participation, governance, privacy and security

Steps
1. Depending on size break the group into smaller groups. Each group should have at least one trainer.
2. Walk each group through the steps involved to create an account. Explain the different option. The pro's anc cons of each role. 
3. Introduce the case, assign roles of the participants and start implementing the case.

Deepening:
- Start with gaining feedback on the experience of the participants. Relate the Hands-on to the first part of the session. Ask questions like: How would Decidim assist you in your actions, can it facilitate the political participation process you are a part of?
- Tease out the key prinicples of the matrix that are important for this context and this group

- Provide input on Decidim:
    - The next steps: Where are we now and where are we going to
    - Decidim as a process and collaborative work
    - Possibilities; get involved in the governance and development process by 1. providing feedback or 2. become part of Meta decidim, the participatory governance structure and way of engaging in the roadmap and strategy of Decidim

Evaluation: 
    Prepare evaluation on the platform and have it in printed form to (for people to take home or for people who feel more comfortable with non digital communication)
    Questionaire or matrix that covers: what worked and what did not on two levels.

        I: Decidim: what works for you? What is missing (functionality)? 
        II:What would you like to add (can be governance, outreach or other things)

Closing 
Closing and referencing other resources, the curricula, other session/agenda
@Alex: Evaluation of the session to? do a plus / delta

